claim.claim-text:
An apparatus for activating a surface of a base material comprising:
a bath vessel (1) being in communication with a water supply source (7) and a gas container (10) filled with carbon dioxide, said bath vessel (1) receiving a stirring element (4) and a predetermined quantity of water therein, wherein a predetermined amount of carbon dioxide is supplied to said vessel so as to form an oxide film removing solution (27), which is a carbonated water (H2CO3);
a jetting head (49) being in communication with said gas container (10) and said bath vessel (1) which sprays said oxide film removing solution (27) and said carbon dioxide onto a surface of a member to be treated (50) disposed in an open space by moving said member to be treated (50) in the back and forth direction, which recovers the used oxide film removing solution (27) and said carbon dioxide;
wherein the surface of said member to be treated (50) is dried after an oxide film is removed, a degreasing treatment and an oxide film removing treatment are executed simultaneously to the surface of said member to be treated (50), and
a separation vessel (57) which introduces the used oxide film removing solution (27) and said carbon dioxide therein and separates the used oxide film removing solution (27) and said carbon dioxide into gas and liquid, and whereby said carbon dioxide and said oxide film removing solution (27) that have been separated are circulated and reproduced and then introduced into said jetting head (49).

